{
  "bead_id": "B-6f3eff2f",
  "title": "Scheduler: serialize within feature tree",
  "agent_type": "planner",
  "description": "Adds an opt-in `SchedulerConfig.serialize_within_feature_tree` boolean flag (default `false`) that forces the scheduler to treat any two mutating beads in the same feature tree as conflicting, regardless of their declared file scopes. Solves the problem of toolchains (Swift/Xcode/SPM) that hold workspace-level locks invisible to file-scope conflict detection. Cross-worktree parallelism is unchanged; only within-worktree packing is disabled when the flag is on.",
